Ada Wodu, Calabar The Cross River State Police Command has confirmed the death of the Divisional Police Officer in charge of the Obudu Division, Gabriel Amawu. He was shot dead on Tuesday in Obudu in circumstances that the police were still trying to unravel as of the time of filing this report. The state Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Irene Ugbo, confirmed the incident to our correspondent on Wednesday in Calabar. “That is (the death of Amawu) what we gathered. I don’t know what really happened. Investigation is ongoing. We don’t know what happened yet. We have sent men there for investigation. No arrest has been made as of the time of filing this report,” she stated. It was gathered that the victim, who was a Deputy Superintendent of Police, was shot dead at his duty post by an unknown person after he allegedly made some arrests. The arrests were allegedly made following suspicion of criminal activities while some youths and students of the Federal College of Education, Obudu, were having fun at the end of their examinations. It was further gathered that some persons stormed the police station in protest over the arrests and in order to disperse the unruly crowd, a policeman allegedly shot into the air. Copyright PUNCH.
